text: Natyrbovo () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Natyrbovskoye Rural Settlement of Koshekhablsky District, Adygea, Russia. The population was 3097 as of 2018. There are 26 streets. == Geography == The village is located on the left bank of the Laba River, 21 km from Koshekhabl. == References == Category:Rural localities in Koshekhablsky District
title: Natyrbovo
